      "email",
      {
        "html": "<p>Hey {first_name, \"there\"},</p><p>Well, it's been a sobering 24 hours. The piece I <a href=\"__GHOST_URL__/2020/09/journalists-do-not-upgrade-to-ios14-today/\">dashed off quickly yesterday morning</a>, warning against iOS14 adoption too quickly, was the most read piece on this site in some months. 🤨</p><p>If we can take anything from that, it's that genuinely useful content, which informs people, and which they can act on (or, in this case, fail to act because of…) means <em>#numbers</em>.</p><p>And today's newsletter is very much on the theme of usefulness.</p>"
      }
